spans.text: The wealth of earth and ocean
The wealth of earth and ocean to secure
to Wealth its jealousy and care
sheep with tender bleat salute my ear
Who pointed steel , with recent slaughter stain , And place in groans and death their cruel joy
In heavenly breasts could ever compassion find
her oft my humble dwelling grace , Humble no more
voice the music of the dawn renews , Its lambent radiance
grasp with hands convulsed and cold
when , in virtue , and in peace grown old , No arts the languid lamp of life restore ; Her let me grasp with hands convulsed and cold , Till every nerve relaxed
soar where only greater joys attend , And bear her image to eternal light
one gleam of comfort warm thy heart
that gentle bosom wound , The joys of heaven would be no joys to me
